{
  "id": "019d317f-3414-76d3-89bd-dbb356369a67",
  "content": "## Clippy Lint Cleanup (Issue #45, PR #48)\n\nFixed all pre-existing clippy lints to enable `cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings` as a clean gate.\n\n### Key patterns used:\n- **`too_many_arguments`**: Introduced `WorkspaceIngestCtx` params struct in `ingest.rs` — idiomatic Rust pattern for functions with 8+ params. Both callers (CLI `workspace.rs` and server `rest.rs`) updated.\n- **`collapsible_if`**: Collapsed nested `if`/`if-let` blocks into let-chains (`if cond && let Pat = expr`) — requires Rust edition 2024.\n- **`lines_filter_map_ok`**: Clippy requires `map_while(Result::ok)` over `filter_map(Result::ok)` for `Lines` iterators to avoid infinite loops on repeated I/O errors.\n- **`unnecessary_map_or`**: `is_some_and()` replaces `map_or(false, ...)`, `is_none_or()` replaces `map_or(true, ...)`.\n- **`manual_checked_ops`**: `checked_div` replaces manual `if x > 0 { y / x }` guards.\n\n### Gotcha discovered:\nWhen fixing clippy lints that block compilation (e.g., `collapsible_if` with `-D warnings`), fixing them unblocks compilation of downstream crates, which may reveal additional pre-existing lints that were previously hidden. The original issue tracked 6 lints but ~28 total surfaced across the workspace.",
